    <text id="F8015T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Curtin discusses possible patronage appointments.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-03-14"><abbr expan="March">Mr</abbr> 14--1860</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <unclear>Bellefonte</unclear>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr> Simon Cameron<lb/>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have <unclear>hoped</unclear> we could manage to retain <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <unclear>Friday</unclear> in the Telegraph office-- I paid him for his <del
                        hand="h1"/> in the campaign, but he charged so little that he could not be
                    expected to remain and especially as he has an office at Washington.</p>
                <p>The office you name would not be in harmony with his tasks, as his training has
                    not been of such as character as to make him familiar with accounts</p>
                <p>The <unclear>Dep. rec</unclear> in addition to the general direction of the
                    hearings of the office <unclear>keep</unclear> all the accounts received the
                        <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> &amp;c &amp;c-</p>
                <p>He is a reliable and faithful man and can be of great service to our party and we
                    must take care of him--</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>A. G. Curtin</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
